From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: GE-Proton <git@localhost>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 12:00:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] mmdevapi,winepulse: Forget Sony controller endpoints on disconnect.

Do not keep disconnected DualSense, DualSense Edge, or DualShock mono speaker endpoints alive for later retargeting.
Spider-Man Remastered can crash when stale controller MMDevice/Pulse state survives a model swap and the game binds its controller-effect stream to an old endpoint.
Treat every Sony controller connection as a fresh device: avoid persisted registry GUIDs for Sony controller backend names, delete endpoint state on removal, notify clients that the endpoint was removed, and stop retargeting existing mono streams to later hotplugged speakers.
This keeps the prefix and Wine process from carrying controller identity across DS, DS Edge, and DualShock disconnect/reconnect cycles.

---
--- a/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
+++ b/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
@@ -107,6 +107,13 @@
